<figureCitation box="[738,850,585,611]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2-28</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,538,653,679]" box="[189,538,653,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,538,653,679]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,538,653,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Morphological observations</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,703,1192]" box="[234,593,703,729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,593,703,729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Light microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[468,585,703,729]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2-24</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,703,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Frustules short, rectangular in girdle view, bent around the transapical axis (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1217,742,768]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2-4</figureCitation>
). Mantle striae often apparently thickened in LM (
<figureCitation box="[608,682,780,806]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Valves narrowly lanceolate with slightly to clearly convex margins and distinctly protracted, rostrate apices (
<figureCitation box="[771,887,819,845]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2-24</figureCitation>
). Valve dimensions (n=30): length 8.5–13.0 µm, width 
<quantity box="[321,461,857,884]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.2 µm</quantity>
. Raphe valve (
<figureCitation box="[638,753,857,884]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 5-15</figureCitation>
) concave with a very narrow linear axial area, almost invisible towards the valve apices, almost not widening towards the central part of the valve. Central area very small, indistinct, bordered by several (usually two) more widely spaced striae. Raphe straight, filiform, almost invisible, with simple proximal raphe endings. Distal raphe fissures not discernible in LM. Striae moderately radiate throughout the entire valve, becoming indiscernible (due to higher density) near the apices. Rapheless valve (
<figureCitation box="[680,808,1049,1076]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 16-24</figureCitation>
) slightly convex with narrow, linear axial area, not or very slightly widening towards the valve centre. Central area almost non-existing, never forming a fascia or subfascia. Central striae very weakly more distantly spaced. Striae weakly radiate throughout, only very slightly more densely spaced near the apices, 
<quantity box="[844,948,1165,1192]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.254999999999999" metricValueMax="8.89" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="in" value="32.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="30.0">30–35 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[955,1034,1165,1191]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1233,1644]" box="[234,762,1233,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,762,1233,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Scanning electron microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[623,754,1233,1259]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 25-28</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1233,1644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Striae in the rapheless valve composed of a series of 3–4 distinct, rounded to square areolae (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1385,1272,1299]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Slit-like areolae apparently never present. Central striae less dense than in the rest of the valve (
<figureCitation box="[1298,1385,1310,1337]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Near the apices, striae only composed of 1–3 rounded areolae (
<figureCitation box="[932,1020,1349,1376]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Mantle areolae elongated, slitlike, often enlarged (
<figureCitation box="[435,524,1387,1414]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Striae on the raphe valve, ca. 
<quantity box="[900,960,1387,1413]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.144" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="in" value="36.0">36 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[969,1048,1388,1414]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, composed of 2–3 irregularly shaped (mostly rounded or elongated rectangular) areolae (
<figureCitation box="[919,1012,1426,1453]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Near the apices, stria density higher (up to 
<quantity box="[356,419,1464,1490]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.652" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="in" value="38.0">38 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[429,512,1464,1491]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
), composed of fewer areolae (
<figureCitation box="[880,971,1464,1491]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Internal areolae openings on both valves covered by hymenes (
<figureCitation box="[529,666,1503,1529]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 27, 28</figureCitation>
). External raphe branches straight terminating in simple, short proximal raphe endings (
<figureCitation box="[485,573,1541,1568]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Distal raphe fissures straight, terminating just beyond the last apical stria (
<figureCitation box="[256,344,1580,1607]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Internally, proximal raphe endings shortly bent into opposite directions (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1307,1580,1606]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Distal raphe endings terminating in small helictoglossae (
<figureCitation box="[786,874,1618,1644]" captionStart="Figs 2-28" captionStartId="4.[189,241,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,678,1784]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 2-28. Achnanthidium indistinctum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 2-4. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 5-15. LM views of raphe valves. 16-24. LM views of rapheless valves. 25. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 26. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 27. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 28. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
