<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,800,414,440]" box="[189,800,414,440]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,800,414,440]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,800,414,440]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ecology, distribution and associated diatom flora</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,460,593]" lastBlockId="5.[189,1399,267,643]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
So far, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalova" authorityYear="2014" box="[279,459,461,487]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="indistinctum">
<emphasis box="[279,459,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. indistinctum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only been found on Livingston Island (South 
<collectingRegion box="[1070,1271,460,487]" country="United Kingdom" name="Shetland Islands" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Shetland Islands</collectingRegion>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,461,487]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
population was observed living on submerged mosses collected in a large lake on the central plateau, located between Midge Lake and Limnopolar lake. The lake had an alkaline pH (7.35) with a low specific conductance value (97 µS/cm) and a high phosphate level (
<quantity box="[963,1048,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mg" value="5.2">5.2 mg</quantity>
/l). The flora in the sample was dominated by several 
<taxonomicName box="[446,637,267,293]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Psammothidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[446,637,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Psammothidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species [
<taxonomicName authority="(Manguin) Bukht. &amp; Round" authorityName="Bukht. &amp; Round" baseAuthorityName="Manguin" box="[746,1222,267,294]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Psammothidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="abundans">
<emphasis box="[746,888,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. abundans</emphasis>
(Manguin) Bukht. &amp; Round
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bukhtiyarova L. &amp; Round F. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref7836" refString="Bukhtiyarova L. &amp; Round F. E. (1996). Revision of the genus Achnanthes sensu lato. Psammothidium, a new genus based on A. marginulatum. Diatom Research 11 (1): 1 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 0269 249 X. 1996.9705361" type="journal article" year="1996">Bukhtiyarova &amp; Round 1996</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(D. E. Kellogg, M. Stuiver, T. B. Kellogg &amp; G. H. Denton) Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalova" authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalova" baseAuthorityName="D. E. Kellogg, M. Stuiver, T. B. Kellogg &amp; G. H. Denton" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Psammothidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="papilio">
<emphasis box="[392,506,306,332]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. papilio</emphasis>
(D.E. Kellogg, M. Stuiver, T.B. Kellogg &amp; G.H. Denton) Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kopalova K. &amp; Vesela J. &amp; Elster J. &amp; Nedbalova L. &amp; Komarek J. &amp; Van de Vijver B." box="[321,581,345,371]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="190 - 208" refId="ref8398" refString="Kopalova K., Vesela J., Elster J., Nedbalova L., Komarek J. &amp; Van de Vijver B. 2012. Benthic diatoms (Bacillariophyta) from seepages and streams on James Ross Island (NW Weddell Sea, Antarctica). Plant Ecology and Evolution 145: 190 - 208. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5091 / plecevo. 2012.639" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kopalová 
<emphasis box="[447,508,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hust.) Bukht. &amp; Round" authorityName="Bukht. &amp; Round" baseAuthorityName="Hust." box="[603,1098,345,371]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Psammothidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="subatomoides">
<emphasis box="[603,796,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. subatomoides</emphasis>
(Hust.) Bukht. &amp; Round
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bukhtiyarova L. &amp; Round F. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref7836" refString="Bukhtiyarova L. &amp; Round F. E. (1996). Revision of the genus Achnanthes sensu lato. Psammothidium, a new genus based on A. marginulatum. Diatom Research 11 (1): 1 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 0269 249 X. 1996.9705361" type="journal article" year="1996">Bukhtiyarova &amp; Round 1996</bibRefCitation>
)], 
<taxonomicName box="[284,393,384,410]" class="Monogenea" family="Capsalidae" genus="Nitzschia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Capsalidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,393,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Nitzschia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[442,563,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">perminuta</emphasis>
(Grunow) M.Peragallo (
<bibRefCitation author="Peragallo M." box="[858,1042,384,410]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="472 - 973" refId="ref9397" refString="Peragallo M. 1903. Le Catalogue General des Diatomees [issued in fascicles at various dates]. Vol. 2: 472 - 973. Clermont-Ferrand." type="journal article" year="1903">Peragallo 1903</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Krasske) Lange-Bert. in Lange-Bertalot &amp; Moser" authorityName="Lange-Bert. in Lange-Bertalot &amp; Moser" baseAuthorityName="Krasske" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Brachysiraceae" genus="Brachysira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1065,1275,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brachysira minor</emphasis>
(Krasske) Lange-Bert. 
<emphasis box="[345,368,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">in</emphasis>
Lange-Bertalot &amp; Moser
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot H. &amp; Moser G." box="[713,1098,422,449]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref8749" refString="Lange-Bertalot H. &amp; Moser G. 1994. Brachysira. Monographie der Gattung. Bibliotheca Diatomologica 29, J. Cramer, Berlin - Stuttgart." type="book" year="1994">Lange-Bertalot &amp; Moser 1994</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grunow) D. G. Mann" authorityName="D. G. Mann" baseAuthorityName="Grunow" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Sellaphoraceae" genus="Sellaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="seminulum">
<emphasis box="[1127,1398,422,448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Sellaphora seminulum</emphasis>
(Grunow) D.G.Mann
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mann D. G." box="[458,598,461,487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref8869" refString="Mann D. G. 1989. The diatom genus Sellaphora: separation from Navicula. British Phycological Journal 24: 1 - 20. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00071618900650011" type="journal article" year="1989">Mann 1989</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<emphasis box="[668,777,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Amphora</emphasis>
sp. It is possible that the species is also present on Signy Island (South 
<collectingCountry box="[434,615,500,527]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Orkney Islands</collectingCountry>
) based on the illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation author="Oppenheim D. R." box="[969,1197,500,526]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1735 - 1748" refId="ref9367" refString="Oppenheim D. R. 1994. Taxonomic studies of Achnanthes (Bacillariophyta) in freshwater maritime antarctic lakes. Canadian Journal of Botany 72: 1735 - 1748." type="journal article" year="1994">Oppenheim (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. The distribution in the Antarctic region and other geographical areas is unclear due to the insufficient discrimination between species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[458,807,578,604]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="minutissimum">
<emphasis box="[458,807,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Achnanthidium minutissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-complex. All published records should be verified in order to know the exact biogeography of this and all other taxa.
</paragraph>
